  <h2>// The Real Cost of Staying on Klaviyo</h2>
  <p>
    The switch from free to paid Klaviyo is not a one-time cost — it's a compounding one. A store that grows from 500 to 10,000 email subscribers in two years will see their Klaviyo bill climb from $0 to approximately $400/month over that period. At 10,000 contacts, Systeme.io's paid plan covers the same list size for $47/month — an annual saving of over $4,000. The full migration guide for moving from Klaviyo to Systeme.io, including how to export flows and re-import your subscriber list, is on the <a href="/replace-klaviyo-free">Replace Klaviyo Free</a> page.
  </p>

  <!-- FAQ ACCORDION -->
  <div class="faq-section">
    <h2>// Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Does Klaviyo free include automation flows?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Yes, Klaviyo's free plan includes access to automation flows including welcome series, abandoned cart, and post-purchase sequences. However, with only 500 contacts and 500 email sends per month on the free plan, the practical utility of automated flows is limited. The moment a flow triggers and sends to a contact, it counts toward your monthly send limit.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Can I remove Klaviyo branding on the free plan?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        No. "Sent by Klaviyo" branding in the email footer cannot be removed on the free plan. To remove it, you must upgrade to a paid Klaviyo plan. Systeme.io's free plan, by comparison, does not include any platform branding in emails.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">What happens when I go over 500 contacts on Klaviyo?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        When your Klaviyo account exceeds 500 contacts, you are automatically moved to the paid tier. Klaviyo will prompt you to add a payment method. If you don't upgrade, sending capabilities are paused until you either upgrade or reduce your contact count below 500 by suppressing or deleting profiles.
      </div>
    </div>

